# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> (aggregate state)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> "aggregate state"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> "an intensive quality representing the physical state of a material, such as solid, liquid, or gasous"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000512> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020116>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> (generation of magnetic field)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> "generation of magnetic field"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> "is a process that occurs as a reaction to change of elctric field or movement of charges and produces a magnetic field"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000070>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> (application of mechanical load)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "application of mechanical load"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "mechanical process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "An application of mechanical load is the process of applying force or stress to a material to observe its response or measure its properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> "is a process in which forces, moments, or imposed displacements to objects or object aggregates occur and/or the equivalent (stresses, strains) to materials or portions of matter"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> (Rohling-Rolle)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> "“Blank.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/blank. Accessed 25 Nov. 2022."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> "Rohling-Rolle"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> "blank role"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> "Role of an object, which is realized in a preparation process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> "Some portion of material, which to be made into something by a further operation."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000534> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> (bulk)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> "bulk"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> "The bulk is a fiat object part that describes the volume or mass of material considered as a whole, often in contrast to surface or interface phenomena."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)))
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000538> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> (Messschieber)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> "https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/caliper"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> "Messschieber"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> "caliper"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> "A measuring device having two usually adjustable arms, legs, or jaws used especially to measure the dimensions of objects, such as diameters or thicknesses"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> "Messgerät mit zwei in der Regel verstellbaren Armen, Schenkeln oder Klemmbacken, das vor allem zur Messung der Abmessungen von Gegenständen, wie z. B. des Durchmessers oder der Dicke, verwendet wird"@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000544> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000547> (change of aggregate state)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000547> "change of aggregate state"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000547> "a phase transformation (change of phase) involving the collective state of particles in portion of matter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000547> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000547> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> (change of temperature)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> "change of temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> "change of temperature is a process in which a particpant changes its temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000549> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> (changing properties of material)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Page 5, 3.1.6 Stoffeigenschaften ändern - Definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Seite 5, 3.1.6 Stoffeigenschaften ändern - Definition"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Stoffeigenschaft Ändern"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "changing properties of material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Changing Of Material  Properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Property Alteration"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "A manufacturing process that modifies the characteristics of the material from which a workpiece is made, including by processes at the submicroscopic or atomic scale, such as atomic diffusion, dislocation formation and movement in the atomic lattice or chemical reactions, whereby the resulting shape changes are not characteristic of these processes."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Ein Herstellungsprozess, der die Merkmale des Materials, aus dem ein Werkstück gefertigt ist, modifiziert, was unter anderem durch Vorgänge im submikroskopischen oder atomaren Bereich erfolgt, wie etwa durch Atomdiffusion, die Versetzungsentstehung und -bewegung im Atomgitter oder durch chemische Reaktionen, wobei die dabei auftretenden Formveränderungen nicht charakteristisch für diese Verfahren sind."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> "Heat Treatment"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> (chemical composition)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> "See the editor note of composition to understand the difference between composition and chemical composition.

See the pattern example of composition to underatand the difference between composition and proportion."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> "chemical composition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> "The chemical composition is an intensive quality of a portion of matter which describes the types and proportions of pure chemical elements in the portion of matter, and it is a subject of some chemical composition data item."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000064> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> "Material has quality chemical composition. Chemical composition is a subject of chemical composition data item. Chemical composition data item has members fraction value specifications (which have a numeral and a unit). Material has part portion of carbon. Material has relational quality mass proportion. Portion of carbon  has relational quality mass proportion. Mass propotion is specified by value fraction value specification. Same approach for all chemical elements."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> (Analyseverfahren für die chemische Zusammensetzung)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> "Analyseverfahren für die chemische Zusammensetzung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> "chemical composition analyzing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> "A structural property analyzing process that determines the chemical composition of a material by identifying and quantifying its constituent elements and compounds."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> "Ein Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das die chemische Zusammensetzung eines Materials bestimmt, indem es dessen Bestandteile und Verbindungen identifiziert und quantifiziert."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000553> (chemical potential)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000553> "chemical potential"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000553> "an intensive quality of a thermodynamic system describing the energy change associated with the addition of a small quantity of a substance to a system at constant temperature and pressure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000553> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000553> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> (Reinigen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8592"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8592"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "Reinigen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "cleaning"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "A separating process that involves removing unwanted material from a surface through cleaning methods, which may include processes like blasting, washing, or chemical cleaning."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "Ein Trennprozess, bei dem unerwünschtes Material von einer Oberfläche durch Reinigungsmethoden entfernt wird, die Verfahren wie Strahlen, Waschen oder chemische Reinigung umfassen können."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> "Chemical Cleaning, Mechanical Cleaning"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000560> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> (Reinigungsgerät)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> "Reinigungsgerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> "cleaning device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> "A device used for removing contaminants from materials or surfaces."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> "Ein Gerät zum Entfernen von Verunreinigungen von Materialien oder Oberflächen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> (Datenverarbeitung)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "The subclass trees of \"Computing Process\" are currently still proposals and serve as a working basis for the discussion round with the simulation/workflow domain experts."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Datenverarbeitung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Rechenprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "computing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "A process that involves the systematic use of computational methods and tools to perform simulations, analyses, or data transformations to achieve specific scientific or engineering goals."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> "Ein Prozess, der die systematische Verwendung von rechnerischen Methoden und Werkzeugen umfasst, um Simulationen, Analysen oder Datenumwandlungen durchzuführen, um spezifische wissenschaftliche oder technische Ziele zu erreichen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000035>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> (crystal structure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "The finite set of periodic geometric arrangements is described e.g. by the 14 possible Bravais Lattices in three-dimensional space."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "crystal structure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "an intensive qualtty of a crystal that embodies the periodic geometric arrangement of entities in a crystal lattice."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> ObjectExactCardinality(1 <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020099>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> (cut function)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "Trennen Funktion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "cut function"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "Schneidfunktion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "A function performed to separate or divide materials using cutting devices."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "Eine Funktion, die ausgeführt wird, um Materialien mit Schneidgeräten zu trennen oder zu teilen."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> (defect density)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> "defect density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> "an intensive quality describing the number of defects per unit volume or area in a material, which can affect its mechanical and electronic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000595> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> (deformation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> "deformation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> "The deformation is a process describing a change in the shape, size, or structure of a material often under the influence of stress or force."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000596> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> (density)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> "density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> "The density is a universal intensive quality representing the unit mass of a portion of matter per unit volume."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> (device)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "Gerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "A device is an object that is designed to perform a specific function or task involving measurement, manipulation, processing, or analysis."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "A physical or virtual entity used to perform a specific function or task, often involving measurement, manipulation, or analysis of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "Ein physisches oder virtuelles Objekt, das verwendet wird, um eine bestimmte Funktion oder Aufgabe auszuführen, häufig im Zusammenhang mit der Messung, Manipulation oder Analyse von Materialien."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> (dielectric constant)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> "dielectric constant"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> "The dielectric constant is an electrical property representing a measure of a material's ability to store electrical energy in an electric field."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621>)
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000604> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> (Dimensions Messprozess)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> "Dimensions Messprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> "dimension measuring process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> "A structural property analyzing process that determines the physical dimensions of a material or object, such as length, width, height, diameter, and thickness, with high accuracy and precision."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> "Ein Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das die physikalischen Dimensionen eines Materials oder Objekts, wie Länge, Breite, Höhe, Durchmesser und Dicke, mit hoher Genauigkeit und Präzision bestimmt."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000611> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> (Zerteilen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8588"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8588"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "Zerteilen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "dividing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "A separating process that involves separating material into distinct parts using techniques like shear cutting, splitting, tearing, or breaking, typically employed in processes where precise control over the cut is less critical."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "Ein Trennprozess, bei dem das Material durch Techniken wie Scherschneiden, Spalten, Reißen oder Brechen in verschiedene Teile zerlegt wird. Es wird in der Regel bei Prozessen eingesetzt, bei denen eine genaue Kontrolle über den Schnitt weniger wichtig ist."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> "Shearing, Cracking"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000614> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000619> (electric potential)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000619> "electric potential"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000619> "an extensvie quality describing the amount of work needed to move a unit charge from a reference point to a specific location in an electric field."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000619> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000619> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620> (electrical conductivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620> "electrical conductivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620> "The electrical conductivity is an electrical property describing the ability of a material to conduct electric current, influenced by its structure and composition."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000620> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621> (electrical property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621> "electrical property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621> "An electrical property is a material property that represents the characteristics of a material that determine its behavior under the influence of an electric field, such as conductivity, resistivity, and permittivity."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> (Elektronenmikroskop)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "“Electron microscope.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/electron%20microscope. Accessed 24 Nov. 2022."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "Elektronenmikroskop"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "electron microscope"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "A microscope that uses a beam of electrons to create high-resolution images of a sample's surface or structure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "An electron-optical instrument in which a beam of electrons is used to produce an enlarged image of a minute object."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> "Ein Gerät, das einen Elektronenstrahl verwendet, um hochauflösende Bilder der Oberfläche oder Struktur einer Probe zu erstellen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> (Elektronenmikroskopie)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> "Elektronenmikroskopie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> "electron microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> "A microscopy process that uses a beam of electrons to create an image of an object, allowing for high-resolution visualization of the material's surface and internal structures."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> "Ein Mikroskopieverfahren, das einen Elektronenstrahl verwendet, um ein Bild eines Objekts zu erzeugen, wodurch eine hochauflösende Visualisierung der Oberfläche und der inneren Strukturen des Materials ermöglicht wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> "An example of an electron microscopy process is Scanning Electron Microscopy (SEM), which provides detailed images of the surface topography and composition of a material. Another example is Transmission Electron Microscopy (TEM), which can visualize the internal structure of a sample at atomic resolution."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> (extensometer)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> "“Extensometer.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/extensometer. Accessed 5 Dec. 2022."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> "extensometer"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> "A device for measuring minute deformations of test specimens caused by tension, compression, bending, or twisting."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> (Ermüdungsprüfverfahren)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "Ermüdungsprüfverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "fatigue testing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "S-N testing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "fatigue testing series"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "Ein Mechanische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das die Fähigkeit eines Materials bewertet, zyklischen Belastungen standzuhalten, und seine Ermüdungslebensdauer und -grenze bestimmt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "Fatigue testing process is a  mechanical property analyzing process that assesses a material's ability to withstand cyclic loading, determining its fatigue life and endurance limit. It must have occurent parts single fatigue tests."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> "Fatigue testing of metal components in bridges to predict their lifespan under repetitive loading conditions."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000638> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025020>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000639> (ferrous metal)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000639> "ferrous metal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000639> "metal that has iron as primary constituent"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000639> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000639> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020026>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> (forming)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Page 4, 3.1.2 Umformen - Definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Seite 4, 3.1.2 Umformen - Definition"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Umformen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "forming"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Shaping"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "A manufacturing process that changes the shape of a solid body through plastic deformation while retaining both mass and structural integrity."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Ein Herstellungsprozess, der durch plastische Umformung die Gestalt eines festen Körpers verändert, wobei sowohl die Masse als auch die strukturelle Integrität erhalten bleiben."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> "Tension Forming, Compression Forming"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> (Formmaschine)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> "Formmaschine"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> "forming machine"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> "A device used for shaping materials under various conditions, including tensile, compressive, and shearing."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> "Ein Gerät zur Formgebung von Materialien unter verschiedenen Bedingungen, einschließlich Zug-, Druck- und Scherbedingungen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> (forming under compressive and tensile conditions)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8584-1"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(dcterms:source <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8584-1"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "Zugdruckumformen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "forming under compressive and tensile conditions"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "A forming process that involves applying both tensile and compressive forces to a material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "Ein Umform Prozess, bei dem sowohl Zug- als auch Druckkräfte auf ein Material ausgeübt werden."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> "Stripping, Deep Drawing, Spinning"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> (Druckumformen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8583-1"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(dcterms:source <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8583-1"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "Druckumformen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "forming under compressive conditions"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "A forming process that involves deforming materials under compressive forces, commonly used in techniques like rolling and die forming where metal is shaped by applying pressure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "Ein Umform Prozess, bei dem Materialien unter Druck verformt werden. Er wird üblicherweise bei Techniken wie Walzen und  Gesenkformen eingesetzt, bei denen Metall durch Druck in Form gebracht wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> "Rolling, Coining"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000646>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> (functional material)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> "Classified by the role in a system."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> "functional material"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> "A functional material F is an engineered material which has the disposition to be used for an object O (O consists of F) and O's function is other/more than mechanical load carrying."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034>)))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000654> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034>))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> (furnace)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> "“Furnace.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/furnace. Accessed 13 Jan. 2023."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> "Ofen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> "furnace"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> "A device that generates and contains high-intensity thermal energy within an insulated enclosure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> "Ein Gerät, das hochintensive thermische Energie innerhalb eines isolierten Gehäuses erzeugt und speichert."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> (kristallit)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "crystallite"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "kristallit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "Korn"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "grain"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "A crystal grain is a crystal that is part of a polycrystal."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020003>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> (grinding machine)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> "Schleifmaschine"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> "grinding machine"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> "A grinding machine is a forming machine that uses an abrasive wheel to remove material from the surface of a workpiece, typically for finishing or precision work."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> "Eine Schleifmaschine ist eine Formmaschine, die ein Schleifrad verwendet, um Material von der Oberfläche eines Werkstücks zu entfernen, typischerweise für Feinarbeiten oder Präzisionsarbeiten."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000667> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> (Verfestigen Durch Umformen)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> "Verfestigen Durch Umformen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> "hardening by forming"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> "A changing properties of material process, that involves altering material properties by mechanical deformation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> "Ein Stoffeigenschaft Ändern Prozess, der die Eigenschaften des Materials durch mechanische Verformung verändert."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> "Sheet Metal Rolling to Achieve Higher Strength."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000772> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000773> (hardness)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000773> "hardness"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000773> "The hardness is a mechanical property used as a measure of a material's resistance to localized plastic deformation, often tested by indentation or scratch methods."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000773> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000773> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> (hardness testing process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> "Härteprüfverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> "hardness testing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> "A mechanical property analyzing process that measures a material's resistance to deformation, typically using indentation methods to determine hardness."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> "Ein Mechanische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das den Widerstand eines Materials gegen Verformung misst und typischerweise Eindringverfahren verwendet, um die Härte zu bestimmen."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> "Hardness testing of steel using the Rockwell method to classify its grade for industrial applications."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000776> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> (Wärmebehandlung)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Official definition can be found in: DIN EN ISO 4885:2018 Wärmebehandlung Page 21, 3.108 Wärmebehandlung - Definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN EN ISO 4885:2018 Wärmebehandlung Seite 21, 3.108 Wärmebehandlung - Definition"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Wärmebehandlung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "heat treatment"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Wärmebehandeln"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "A changing properties of material process in which a solid (ferrous) product is fully or partially exposed to specific time-temperature sequences through a series of process steps with the aim of modifying its properties and/or its internal structure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Ein Stoffeigenschaft Ändern Prozess, bei dem durch eine Reihe von Verfahrensschritten ein festes (Eisen-)Produkt ganz oder teilweise bestimmten Zeit-Temperatur-Abfolgen ausgesetzt wird, mit dem Ziel, seine Eigenschaften und/oder seine innere Struktur zu modifizieren."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> "Annealing, Ageing, Hardening"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000550>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> (Wärmebehandlungsgerät)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> "Wärmebehandlungsgerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> "heat treatment device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> "A device used for treating materials through heating and cooling processes to alter their properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> "Ein Gerät zur Behandlung von Materialien durch Erwärmungs- und Abkühlungsprozesse zur Veränderung ihrer Eigenschaften."@de)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000055>))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000780> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000055>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> (Induktionsofen)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> "Induktionsofen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> "induction furnace"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> "An induction furnace is a furnace that heats materials using electromagnetic induction, generating heat directly within the material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> "Ein Induktionsofen ist ein Ofen, der Materialien durch elektromagnetische Induktion erhitzt, wobei die Wärme direkt im Material erzeugt wird."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000791> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000655>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> (lasercutter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> "Laserschneider"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> "lasercutter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> "A device that utilizes laser beams to create precise cuts in various materials such as wood, plastic, metal, etc."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> "Ein Gerät, das Laserstrahlen verwendet, um präzise Schnitte in verschiedenen Materialien wie Holz, Kunststoff, Metall usw. zu erzeugen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> (light microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> "Lichtmikroskopie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> "light microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> "An optical microscopy process that uses visible light and lenses to magnify and visualize specimens, enabling the study of the microstructure and morphology of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> "Ein optisches Mikroskopieverfahren, das sichtbares Licht und Linsen verwendet, um Proben zu vergrößern und zu visualisieren, wodurch die Untersuchung der Mikrostruktur und Morphologie von Materialien ermöglicht wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> "An example of a light microscopy process is Confocal Laser Scanning Microscopy, which uses laser light to scan specimens and create high-resolution, three-dimensional images. Another example is Fluorescence Microscopy, which uses fluorescent dyes to label specific components of the specimen, allowing for the visualization of structures that are otherwise difficult to see. A third example is Polarized Light Microscopy, which utilizes polarized light to enhance contrast in samples with birefringent properties, such as crystalline materials."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000819> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> (Spanen Mit Geometrisch Bestimmten Schneiden)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8589-0"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8589-0"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "Spanen Mit Geometrisch Bestimmten Schneiden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "machining geometrically defined"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "A separating process that involves removing material with a tool that has a defined shape and sharp edges, such as in sawing and drilling operations."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "Ein Trennprozess, bei dem Material mit einem Werkzeug mit definierter Form und scharfen Kanten entfernt wird, wie z. B. beim Sägen und Bohren."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> "Drilling, Turning"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000822> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> (Spanen Mit Geometrisch Unbestimmten Schneiden)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8589-0"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8589-0"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "Spanen Mit Geometrisch Unbestimmten Schneiden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "machining geometrically undefined"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "A separating process that involves removing material using tools with undefined cutting edges, such as grinding or abrasive machining, where the exact shape of the cutting part isn't clearly defined."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "Ein Trennprozess, bei dem Material mit Werkzeugen mit undefinierten Schneiden abgetragen wird, wie z. B. beim Schleifen oder bei der abrasiven Bearbeitung, bei der die genaue Form des zu schneidenden Teils nicht klar definiert ist."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> "Grinding, Blasting"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000823> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825> (magnetic property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825> "magnetic property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825> "A magnetic property is a material property representing characteristics that describe how a material responds to magnetic fields, such as permeability and coercivity."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> (Magnetisierungsgerät)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> "Magnetisierungsgerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> "magnetizing device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> "A device used for inducing a magnetic field in materials to alter their magnetic properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> "Ein Gerät zur Induktion eines Magnetfelds in Materialien, um deren magnetische Eigenschaften zu verändern."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000827> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> (Magnetische Elektrische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> "Magnetische Elektrische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> "magneto electrical property analyzing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> "An assay that investigates the magnetic and electrical properties of materials, including conductivity, resistivity, permittivity, permeability, and magnetization."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> "Eine Analyse, die die magnetischen und elektrischen Eigenschaften von Materialien untersucht, einschließlich Leitfähigkeit, Widerstand, Permittivität, Permeabilität und Magnetisierung."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000070>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> (manufacturing process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "Manufacturing processes alternate qualities of materials, i.e., a value specification of some quality of a material entity, which is a specified input to the process, cannot be the same as a value specification of the same quality of another material entity, which is a specified output of the process. 

Unfortunately it is not possible to write down such axiom based on OWL. Semi-working solution are the temporally qualified continuants + SPARQL constrains."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "Herstellungsprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "manufacturing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "A planned process that is driven by the primary intent to transform objects
A manufacturing process is always a transformative process."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "Ein geplannter Prozess, der von der primären Absicht angetrieben wird, Objekte zu transformieren. Ein Herstellungsprozess ist immer ein Transformationsprozess."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000035> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000035>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> (map)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> "map"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> "A map is a 2D information content entity describing a representation of spatial data or relationships, often used in material science for visualizing properties or distributions."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000502>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> (mechanical property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> "The axiom that mechanical property has realization some application of mechanical load treats only conventional materials and not such effects as magnetostriction etc."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> "mechanical property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> "A mechanical property is a material property which is a characteristic of material M. Mechanical property has realization in a stimulating process (in most cases, application of mechanical load), and the stimulating process is an occurent part of another process, in which an object O that is an instance of M participates."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000522>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> (mechanical property analyzing process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> "Mechanische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> "mechanical property analyzing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> "An assay that evaluates the mechanical characteristics of materials, such as strength, hardness, elasticity, and tensile properties, often through tests that measure response to forces and loads."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> "Eine Analyse, die die mechanischen Eigenschaften von Materialien bewertet, wie z.B. Festigkeit, Härte, Elastizität und Zugfestigkeit, oft durch Tests, die die Reaktion auf Kräfte und Lasten messen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000070>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> (metal)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> "Classified by morphology."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> "metal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> "A metal is an engineered material representing a class of materials characterized by high electrical and thermal conductivity, ductility, and metallic bonding."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000852> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000663> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_33521> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002>)))))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> (crystallographic texture)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> "typically observed through crystallographic analysis"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> "crystallographic texture"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> "an intensive quality describing the arrangement and orientation of grains in a polychrystal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177>) ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000004> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> (microscope)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> "Mikroskop"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> "microscope"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> "A device used to magnify and view small objects or details that are not visible to the naked eye."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> "Ein Gerät zur Vergrößerung und Betrachtung kleiner Objekte oder Details, die mit bloßem Auge nicht sichtbar sind."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> (Mikroskopie Verfahren)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "Mikroskopie Verfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "microscopy process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "Ein Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das verschiedene Arten von Mikroskopietechniken verwendet, um die Mikrostruktur und Morphologie von Materialien auf verschiedenen Ebenen zu visualisieren und zu analysieren."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "Microscopy process that uses various types of microscopy techniques to visualize and analyze the microstructure and morphology of materials at different scales."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "Electron microscopy, which provides detailed images at high resolution; ion microscopy, which offers high-precision imaging and material milling capabilities; and optical microscopy, which uses visible light to study e.g. the microstructure of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> "Mikroskopie"@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000070>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> (microstructure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> "The focus of interest when looking at an object through the microstructure perspective is often its morphology."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> "microstructure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> "A microstructure is a portion of matter that represents the small-scale structure of a material, including grains, phases, and defects, visible under a microscope."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> (Optisches Mikroskop)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> "Optisches Mikroskop"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> "optical microscope"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> "A microscope that uses visible light and lenses to magnify and view small objects or details."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> "Ein Mikroskop, das sichtbares Licht und Linsen verwendet, um kleine Objekte oder Details zu vergrößern und zu betrachten."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000874> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000855>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> (optical microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> "Optische Mikroskopie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> "optical microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> "A microscopy process that uses visible light and lenses to magnify and image a specimen, widely used for examining the microstructure and morphology of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> "Ein Mikroskopieverfahren, das sichtbares Licht und Linsen verwendet, um eine Probe zu vergrößern und abzubilden, und weit verbreitet zur Untersuchung der Mikrostruktur und Morphologie von Materialien ist."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> "An example is Light Microscopy."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000875> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000856>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> (pole figure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> "pole figure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> "A pole figure is a map depicting a 2D stereographic projection which represents crystallographic orientations of grains in a polycrystalline material in respect to the sample's reference frame."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000885> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> (polishing machine)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> "Poliermaschine"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> "polishing machine"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> "A polishing machine is a forming machine that smooths the surface of a material by rubbing it with a tool, abrasive, or chemical."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> "Eine Poliermaschine ist eine Formmaschine, die die Oberfläche eines Materials durch Reiben mit einem Werkzeug, Schleifmittel oder Chemikalien glättet."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000886> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000648>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> (connected material entity aggregate)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> "connected material entity aggregate"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of separate material entities, which adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions that go beyond gravity."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> "the atoms of a molecule, the molecules forming the membrane of a cell, the epidermis in a human body"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> (disconnected material entity aggregate)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> "disconnected material entity aggregate"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of scattered (i.e. spatially separated) material entities, which do not adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions but, instead, relate to one another merely on grounds of metric proximity. The material entities are separated from one another through space or through other material entities that do not belong to the group."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> "a heap of stones, a colony of honeybees, a group of synapses, the trees of a forest, the canopy of a forest, the fish of a shoal, a group of commuters on the subway, the patients in a hospital"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> (pressure)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> "The pressure is commonly measured in Pascals."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> "pressure"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> "an intensive quality describing the force exerted per unit area in or on a material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> (Urformen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Page 4, 3.1.1 Urformen - Definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Seite 4, 3.1.1 Urformen - Definition"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Urformen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "primary shaping"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Primary Forming"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "A manufacturing process that creates a defined workpiece from shapeless material by producing cohesion, whereby the characteristic properties of the material become visible in the end product."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Ein Herstellungsprozess, der aus formlosem Stoff durch das Herstellen von Kohäsion ein definiertes Werkstück schafft, wobei die charakteristischen Eigenschaften des Materials im Endprodukt sichtbar werden."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> "Casting, Sintering"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> (primary shaping from the liquid state)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> "Urformen Aus Dem Flüssigen Zustand"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> "primary shaping from the liquid state"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> "A primary shaping process that involves forming materials from a liquid state."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> "Ein Urformprozess, der das Formen von Materialien aus einem flüssigen Zustand beinhaltet."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> "Casting of molten metal into molds."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000899>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> (Abtragen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8590"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8590"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "Abtragen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "removing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "A separating process that involves removing material through thermal, chemical and electrochemical methods."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "Ein Trennprozess, bei dem Material durch thermische, chemische und elektrochemische Methoden abgetragen wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> "Electrical Discharge Machining, Thermal Ablation"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000914> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> (scanning electron microscope)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> "Rasterelektronenmikroskop"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> "scanning electron microscope"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> "A scanning electron microscope (SEM) is a measuring device that produces high-resolution images of a sample surface by scanning it with a focused beam of electrons."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> "Ein Rasterelektronenmikroskop (REM) ist ein Messgerät, das hochauflösende Bilder einer Probenoberfläche erzeugt, indem es sie mit einem fokussierten Elektronenstrahl abtastet."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000922> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000624>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> (Trennen)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8580:2003-9 Fertigungsverfahren, Page 4, 3.1.3 Trennen - Definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "Trennen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "separating"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "A manufacturing process in which the bond between objects is broken, resulting in a partial or complete reduction in cohesion."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "Ein Herstellungsprozess, bei dem die Bindung zwischen Objekten aufgehoben wird, was zu einer teilweisen oder vollständigen Verringerung der Kohäsion führt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "Disassembling, Removal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> "Cutting"@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> (Simulationsprozess)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> "Simulationsprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> "simulation process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> "A computing process that models the behavior of a system over time using mathematical or computational techniques."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> "Ein Datenverarbeitungsprozess, der das Verhalten eines Systems im Laufe der Zeit mit mathematischen oder rechnerischen Techniken modelliert"@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000583>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000942> (specific surface area)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000942> "specific surface area"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000942> "an intensive quality embodying the total surface area of a material per unit of mass or volume."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000942> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000942> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> (spectroscopy process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> "Spektroskopie Verfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> "spectroscopy process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> "A structural property analyzing process that measures the interaction of electromagnetic radiation with matter to determine e.g. the composition, structure, and other properties of materials."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> "Ein Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das die Wechselwirkung von elektromagnetischer Strahlung mit Materie misst, um die Zusammensetzung, Struktur und physikalischen Eigenschaften von Materialien zu bestimmen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025001>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> (spectrum)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> "spectrum"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> "A spectrum is a 1-D information content entity that describes the range of wavelengths or frequencies of a physical property, often used in reference to light, sound, or electromagnetic radiation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000501>)
DisjointClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000946> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> (stimulating process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> "stimulating process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> "The stimulating process is a process describing the application of an external influence, such as force, heat, or radiation, to study material response."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001>)))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000950> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000001>))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> (strength)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> "strength"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> "The strength is a material property describing the maximum stress a material can withstand before failure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> "The strength is a mechanical property describing the maximum stress a material can withstand before failure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000952> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000848>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> (Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> "Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> "structural property analyzing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> "An assay that examines the external and internal structure and morphology of materials, including the arrangement of atoms, crystals, grains, and phases, often using techniques like microscopy and diffraction."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> "Eine Analyse, die die äußere und innere Struktur und Morphologie von Materialien untersucht, einschließlich der Anordnung von Atomen, Kristallen, Körnern und Phasen, oft unter Verwendung von Techniken wie Mikroskopie und Beugung."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000070>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> (surface layer (fiat object part))

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> "surface layer (fiat object part)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> "A surface layer (fiat object part) is a fiat object part that is part of only object. The surface layer is the three dimensional region defining the outermost layer of an object, where surface-interactions with other material entities occur. What is considered as the surface is thus defined by the interaction process."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> "When considering optical properties of a surface layer (fiat object part) of a polished piece of metal we likely consider a different three dimensional spatial region than when considering the scratch hardness properties of the same polished piece of metal."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000965> ObjectAllValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ObjectUnionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> (temperature)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "The concept refers to an absolute temperature, not to be mistaken with temperature difference."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "To express that an object has a temperature, the property 'intensive bearer of' can be used. It implies a chain of: object consists of some portion of matter and portion of matter bearer of some temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "The temperature is a fundamental intensive quality representing the average atomic or molcular movement or vibration of a portion of matter."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> (Temperaturänderungsfunktion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> "Temperaturänderungsfunktion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> "temperature change function"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> "A function in heat treatment performed to induce changes in temperature to alter material properties."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> "Eine Unterfunktion der Wärmebehandlung, die durchgeführt wird, um Temperaturänderungen hervorzurufen, um die Materialeigenschaften zu verändern."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000969> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> (tensile testing machine)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> "Zugprüfmaschine"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> "tensile testing machine"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> "A device used to test the tensile strength and elongation of materials by applying a stretching force."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> "Ein Gerät zur Prüfung der Zugfestigkeit und Dehnung von Materialien durch Anwendung einer Dehnkraft."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> "Ein Gerät zur Prüfung der Zugfestigkeit und Dehnung von Materialien durch Anwendung einer Dehnkraft."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000973> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> (Zugprüfverfahren)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "Zugprüfverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "tensile testing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "A Mechanical Property Analyzing Process that determines a material's response to tensile forces, measuring its tensile strength, elongation, and Young's modulus."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "A mechanical property analyzing process that determines a material's response to tensile forces, measuring its tensile strength, elongation, and Young's modulus."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "Ein Mechanische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das die Reaktion eines Materials auf Zugkräfte bestimmt und seine Zugfestigkeit, Dehnung und seinen Elastizitätsmodul misst."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> "Tensile testing of polymer films to ensure they can stretch without breaking in packaging applications"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000849>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000978> (thermal conductivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000978> "thermal conductivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000978> "The thermal conductivity is a thermal property describing the ability of a material to conduct heat."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000978> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000978> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> (thermal property)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> "thermal property"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> "A thermal property is a material property representing attributes of a material that describe its behavior under temperature changes, such as thermal conductivity and expansion."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000981> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992> (time series)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992> "time series"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992> "A time series is a 1-D information content entity defined by a sequence of data points collected or recorded at successive time intervals, used for analyzing temporal properties or trends."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000992> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000501>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> (ultrasonic cleaner)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "Ultraschallreiniger"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "ultrasonic cleaner"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "A device that uses ultrasound and a cleaning solvent to clean delicate or complex items."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "An Ultrasonic Cleaner is a Cleaning Device that uses high-frequency sound waves and a cleaning solvent to remove contaminants from delicate or complex items."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "Ein Gerät, das Ultraschall und ein Reinigungsmittel verwendet, um empfindliche oder komplexe Gegenstände zu reinigen."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> "Ein Ultraschallreiniger ist ein Reinigungsgerät, das Hochfrequenzschallwellen und ein Reinigungsmittel verwendet, um Verunreinigungen von empfindlichen oder komplexen Gegenständen zu entfernen."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000997> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000561>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> (waterjet cutter)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> "Wasserstrahlschneider"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> "waterjet cutter"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> "A device that utilizes a high-pressure stream of water or a water stream with abrasive particles to cut materials such as metal, stone, plastic, etc."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> "Ein Gerät, das einen Hochdruckwasserstrahl oder einen Wasserstrahl mit abrasiven Partikeln verwendet, um Materialien wie Metall, Stein, Kunststoff usw. zu schneiden."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> (x-ray analyzing process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> "Röntgen Analyseverfahren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> "x-ray analyzing process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> "A structural property analyzing process that uses X-rays to investigate the internal structure, composition, and properties of materials by measuring the interaction of X-rays with the sample."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> "Ein Struktur Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren, das Röntgenstrahlen verwendet, um die innere Struktur, Zusammensetzung und Eigenschaften von Materialien zu untersuchen, indem die Wechselwirkung der Röntgenstrahlen mit der Probe gemessen wird."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> (x-ray diffraction process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "Beugungsprozess"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "x-ray diffraction process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "An X-ray analyzing process, that involves the interaction of X-rays with the crystalline structure of a material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "Ein Röntgenanalyseverfahren, das die Wechselwirkung von Röntgenstrahlen mit der kristallinen Struktur eines Materials umfasst."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "XRD is used to e.g. determine the crystal structure of newly synthesized compounds to determine the crystal lattice arrangement."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> "XRD"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000591>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001016> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> (Röntgen-Mapping)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> "Röntgen-Mapping"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> "x-ray mapping"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> "An X-ray analyzing process, that generates a spatial distribution map of the elements within a specimen by scanning the sample with an electron or X-ray beam and detecting the emitted X-rays, providing detailed compositional information across the sample's surface."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> "Ein Röntgenanalyseverfahren, das eine räumliche Verteilungskarte der Elemente innerhalb einer Probe erstellt, indem die Probe mit einem Elektronen- oder Röntgenstrahl abgetastet und die emittierten Röntgenstrahlen detektiert werden, wodurch detaillierte Zusammensetzungsinformationen über die Oberfläche der Probe geliefert werden."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> "An example of an X-ray Mapping process is X-ray Absorption Spectroscopy, X-ray Fluorescence, or X-ray Photoelectron Spectroscopy."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001017> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> (x-ray microanalysis)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> "Röntgen-Mikroanalyse"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> "x-ray microanalysis"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> "An X-ray analyzing process that determines the elemental composition and chemical properties of a specimen by detecting and analyzing the characteristic X-rays emitted from the sample when it is irradiated with a focused electron beam."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> "Ein Röntgenanalyseverfahren, das die elementare Zusammensetzung und chemischen Eigenschaften einer Probe bestimmt, indem die charakteristischen Röntgenstrahlen detektiert und analysiert werden, die von der Probe emittiert werden, wenn sie mit einem fokussierten Elektronenstrahl bestrahlt wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> "An example for X-ray Microanalysis process is Energy Dispersive X-ray Spectroscopy."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001014>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001018> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000551>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> (Röntgenspektroskopie)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> "Röntgenspektroskopie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> "x-ray spectroscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> "A spectroscopy process, that analyzes the interaction of X-rays with matter to determine the material's composition and structure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> "Ein Spektroskopie Verfahren, das die Wechselwirkung von Röntgenstrahlen mit Materie analysiert, um die Zusammensetzung und Struktur des Materials zu bestimmen."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> "Examples are e.g. X-ray absorption spectroscopy, X-ray emission spectroscopy, and X-ray reflection spectroscopy."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001019> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000945>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> (Röntgenbeugungsgerät)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> "Röntgenbeugungsgerät"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> "x-ray diffractometer"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> "An X-Ray diffractometer is a measuring device that determines the crystal structure of materials by analyzing the diffraction patterns of X-rays passed through a sample."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> "Ein Röntgenbeugungsgerät ist ein Messgerät, das die Kristallstruktur von Materialien durch Analyse der Beugungsmuster von durch eine Probe geleiteten Röntgenstrahlen bestimmt."@de)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001020> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

