# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> (magnetic field alternating frequency)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> "TODO: the axiom is a thin ice. Decide if application of the MF MUST be a part of an assay")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> "magnetic field alternating frequency"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> "Magnetic field alternating current is a process attribute of an application of magnetic field describing how many times per second the applied magnetic field changes its direction."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> "400 Hz frequency of an Epstein measurment"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025007>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> ObjectUnionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000521> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> (plot)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "plot"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "A plot is a 2-D information content entity describing a dependency of one variable on another."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> "B-H curve, stress-strain curve"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000502>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> (B-H curve)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> "B-H curve"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> "B-H curve is a plot which describes the dependency of magnetic flux density B on magnetic field strength H in soft and hard magnetic materials."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000005> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> (stress-strain curve)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> "stress-strain curve"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> "Stress-strain curve is a plot which describes the dependency of deformation in a sample on the applied stress (force per unit area)."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000004>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> (3D)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> "3D"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> "A three-dimensional information content entity is a representation or analysis, commonly applied in studying material properties in its volume or describing a dependency of one variable on two other variables"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> (orientation distribution function)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "orientation distribution function"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "ODF"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> "Orientation distrubution function (ODF) is a 3D information content entity which quantitively describes texture (preferred crystallographic orientation of grains) in polycrystalline materials. ODF can be caclulated from pole figures obtained from the diffraction patterns."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000008> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000007>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> (EBSD map)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> "EBSD map"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> "EBSD (electron backscatter diffraction) map represents a information content entity which is determined analytically from data obtrained from EBSD characterization. EBSD map provides information about grain size and grain orientation."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000834>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> (quasi-static (DC) characterization of magnetic properties)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "TODO: The definition has to be refined. 
TODO: Write axioms based on the definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "quasi-static (DC) characterization of magnetic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "Quasi-static (DC) characterization is a magnetic properties analyzing process for soft magnetic sheet materials which aims to determine a static magnetic curve of the tested material. During the test, the current in the primary winding is changed slowly, thus the frequency of a magnetic field remains low, i.e., below 0.01 Hz. The output of the quasi-static characterization of magnetic properties  is a static B-H curve, which  provides information on hysteresis loss Ph, saturation induction Bsat, coercivity Hc, remanence Br, and maximum permeability µmax. During DC characterization primarily domain wall motion and pinning effects play role."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> "Measurement of hysteresis losses; measurement of saturation magnetic induction at specified maximal magnetic field, e.g., 5000 A/m."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000010> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> ObjectHasValue(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UO_0000106>) DataSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001937> DatatypeRestriction(xsd:decimal xsd:maxExclusive "1.0"^^xsd:decimal)))))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> (dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "Dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties is a magnetic properties analyzing process for soft magnetic sheet materials which aims to determine the total energy loss of a tested material at specific frequency and magnetic flux density. During the test, the current in the primary winding is changed with frequency between 50-400 Hz to ensure sinusoidal waveform of the magnetic flux density at Bpeak. The output of the dynamic characterization of magnetic properties  is a  B-H curve, which  provides information on total core loss Ptot and dynamic permeability µdyn."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "TODO: refine defintion
TODO: write axioms"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "dynamic (AC) characterization of magnetic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> "Measurement of total power (iron) loss at given current frequency and maximal magnetic induction, e.g. 50 Hz and 1.5 T, or 400 Hz and 1.0 T"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000011> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000009> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000003> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> ObjectHasValue(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UO_0000106>) DataSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001937> DatatypeRestriction(xsd:decimal xsd:minExclusive "1.0"^^xsd:decimal)))))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> (magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> "magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> "Magnetic property analyzing process using Epstein frame is a standardized assay which uses Epstein frame to test magnetic properties of soft magnetic materials, where several (how many) strips are stacked."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000183>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000012> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> (magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> "magnetic property analyzing process using single sheet tester is an assay for determining magnetic properties of soft mangetic materials, where magnetic field H is applied to a single sheet."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000184>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000013> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> (magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> "magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> "Magnetic property analyzing process using thoroidal core is an assay for determing magnetic properties of soft magnetic materials, where the sample has closed wound ring core shape. As the ring shape does not have any air gaps or joint losses, this testing procedure provides information on most intrinsic material properties."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000185>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000014> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000829>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> (cold rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> "Cold rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce thickness of a metallic sheet. Cold rolling takes place at room temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> "cold rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000015> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> (hot rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> "Hot rolling is a rolling process which aims to reduce the thickness of a sheet material. Hot rolling  takes place at temperatures above alloy's recrystallization temperature."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> "hot rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000016> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> (occurence of magnetic flux)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> "Occurence of magnetic flux  is a process that (realizes??) responds with magnetic flux in the material when some magnetic field is applied."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> "occurence of magnetic flux"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(owl:deprecated <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000017> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> (recrystallization)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "follows  Arrhenius equation.
Has part grain growth and recovery."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "recrystallization"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> "Recrystallization is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which deformed grains are replaced by new defect-free grains. Recrystallization is a thermally activated process, i.e., it requires sufficiently high temperatures for the process to occur. Thus, recrystallization is a process which is part of annealing heat treatment."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000018> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> (recovery)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> "recovery"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> "Recovery is a naturally occuring process which occurs in metallic materials and during which the reduction of stored deformation energy in grains occurs due to the removal and rearragement of crystal structure defects (dislocations). Recovery is a part of recrystallization process, thus it is a thermally activated process, which occurs during annealing heat treatment."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000019> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> (grain growth)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> "grain growth"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> "Grain growth is a process which occurs in polycrystalline materials. The driving force of grain growth is reduction of the interal energy via reduction of the total grain boundary. Grain growth is a thermally activated process which occurs after recovery and (primary) recrystallization."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000020> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> (domain wall motion)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> "domain wall motion"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> "Domain wall motion is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials due to the external stimulus such as applied magnetic field."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025009>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> (domain wall pinning)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> "domain wall pinning"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> "Domain wall pinning is a naturally occuring process which occurs in ferromagnetic materials when domain wall montion is temporally inhibited due to an energy barrier."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000022> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025009>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> (rolling)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> "Rolling is a shaping process in which material is passed through under a roll with the goal of reducing the thickness of a semi-finished object. After rolling the mateiral deformed microstructure, which is characterized by elongated defomed grains, high dislocation density, high internal strains, and preferred grain orientation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> "rolling"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000649>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> (strip-casting)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "The defintion has potential"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "strip-casting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> "Strip-casting is a primary shaping from fluid state process for metals and alloys. During Strip-casting the melt flows between two rolls resulting in the strip."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000024> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000906>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> (Schmieden)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "Schmieden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "forging"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> "Forging is a pressure forming process of metals and alloys. During forging the material is heated to forging temperature and formed to the desired form using either hammers and anvils or heat-resistant upper and lower dies."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000025> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000650>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> (normalizing)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> "normalizing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> "Normalizing is a heat treatment process which aims to create uniform grain structure and improve toughness of an alloy. During normalizing the material is heated above its critical temperature, kept at this temperature for a period of time, and then cooled in the air."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000026> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> (annealing)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> "annealing"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> "Annealing is a heat treatment process which aims to soften an alloy and relieve internal stresses. The material is heated above its critical termperature at which recrystallization occurs. After holding the material at the temperature, it is cooled in a slow and controlled way usually inside an oven."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000027> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000779>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> (longitudinal direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> "longitudinal direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> "Longitudinal direction is a rolled sheet direction along the dimension in which an anisotropic material property is measured. Longitudinal direction might be parallel to the rolling or transversal direction of a rolled material, and it is always normal to the rolling direction."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000094>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> (scanning electron microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "scanning electron microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "https://www.thermofisher.com/de/de/home/materials-science/learning-center/applications/sem-tem-difference.html")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "SEM"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> "Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) is a type of electron microscopy where a focused beam of electrons scans the surface of an object. An image is created by detecting electrons reflected from the surface. Thus, SEM provides information on the surface and composition of the sample."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000032> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> (rolling direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> "TODO: 
1. Refine definition
2. Maybe remove the categorical values")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> "rolling direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> "Rolling direction is a rolled sheet direction that is specified by rolling direction (RD)."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001> ObjectHasValue(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000028>)))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000001>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000094>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000068> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000036>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> (electron backscatter diffraction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "electron backscatter diffraction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "Electron Backscatter Diffraction (EBSD) is a SEM based technique for characterizing  material's local microstructure. EBSD provides an information about phases and their distribution in the material, grain structure, grain size, grain boundary, texture  (crystallographic orientation of individual grains), and local strain variation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "https://www.ebsd.com/ebsd-explained/what-is-ebsd")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> "EBSD"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000153>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000034> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/cryo/CRYO_0000042>))

