# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> (waterjet cutting)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> "waterjet cutting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> "Waterjet cutting is a cutting process, where waterjet cutter is a participant and it realizes some cutting function."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0001007> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>)))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000037> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> (number of strips)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> "number of strips"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> "Number of strips is a extensive quality of a disconnected material entity aggregate which has parts individual strips of an electrical sheet and characterizes how many strips or sheets are present in a packet, used for Epstein or thoroidal core measurement or construction of stators and rotors"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000038> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> (tensile strength in the rolling direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> "An instance belonging to the class should be rather inferred as asserted."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> "tensile strength in the rolling direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> "Tensile strength in to the rolling direction is a tensile strength which is measured on a sample cut parallel to the rolling direction."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000122> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> "false"^^xsd:boolean)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/tto/TTO_0000053> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(ObjectInverseOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001938>) ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000109> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000312> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000974> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000040> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025998> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> DataHasValue(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001937> "0"^^xsd:integer)))))))))))))))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000039> <https://w3id.org/pmd/tto/TTO_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> (intrinsic reference frame)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> "Note that intrinsic reference frame is \"grounded into\" the material entity, i.e., it moves with it, and if material entity ceases to exist so will its intrinsic reference frame."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> "intrinsic reference frame"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> "Intrinsic reference frame is an immaterial entity  which is geometric basis of some material entity, e.g., material or an object. Intrinsic reference frame has parts continuant fiat boundaries, e.g., specific directions or planes which uniquely define this reference frame."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000141>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000140>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000041> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000074> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> (laser cutting)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "laser cutting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> "Laser cutting is a cutting process, where lasercutter is a participant and it realizes some cutting function."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000817> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000592>)))))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000042> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000927>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> (texture parameter Aθ)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "texture parameter Aθ"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "doi:10.1155/2008/173083")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> "Texture parameter is a intensive quality which quantifies crystallographic texture in materials. Texture parameter is defined as a minimun angle between the magnitization vector and the closest <100> direction in a crystal. Texture parameter can be derived from orientation distribution function (ODF) by integrating ODF f(g) multiplied by Aθ(g) over orientations dg."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000043> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> (direction averaged texture parameter A)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "direction averaged texture parameter A"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "doi:10.1155/2008/173083")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> "Direction averaged texture parameter A is a intensive quality which quantifies crystallographic texture in materials, which are utilized in applications where applied magnetic field is equally distributed in the rolling plane (RP) of the material. Direction averaged texture parameter A is derived from the texture parameter Aθ by integrating Aθ over dθ. For noriented electrical steels it can be simplified as (A0 + 2*A45 + A90) / 4, where A0, A45, and A90 are values of texture parameter Aθ for an applied magnetic field which encloses an angle of 0, 45, and 90 with the rolling direction, respectively."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000044> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> (texture factor)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> "texture factor"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> "Texture factor is an intensive quality used to quantify texture in materials. It is determined as sum of volume fractions of Goss and Cube texture components divided by the volume fraction of γ-fiber orientations."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000045> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> (transmission electron microscopy)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "transmission electron microscopy"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "https://www.thermofisher.com/de/de/home/materials-science/learning-center/applications/sem-tem-difference.html")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "TEM"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> "Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) is a type of electron microscopy where a beam of electrons goes through a sample. An image is created by detecting electrons transmitted through the sample. Thus, TEM provides information on the crystal structure, morphology and stress state of the sample"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000046> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> (electron probe microanalysis)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "electron probe microanalysis"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "EPMA"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> "Electron probe microanalysis (EPMA) is a technique to non-destructively determine the chemical element composition of small volumes of solid materials. In EPMA an electron beam is focued on a single point of a surface of a sample. The energy of an electron beam is high enough for electrons to pentrate deeper in the sample causing excitation of characteristic x-rays. An x-ray spectrometer detects those characteristic x-rays providing information about materials chemical composition."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000047> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000552>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> (coercivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "A low H_c​ is desirable for soft magnetic materials like electrical steel, indicating easy magnetization and demagnetization"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "coercivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "coercive field strength"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "Coercivity is a magnetic property which is stimulated under an application of magnetic field. It describesthe value of the magnetic field strength H required to reduce the Magnetic Flux Density B back to zero after the material has been driven to the saturation of magnetic flux density B_sat."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> "Hc"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000048> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> (magnetic induction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "magnetic induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "magnetic flux density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "Magnetic induction is a magnetic property stimulated by an applied extermal magnetic field H. It characterizes the response of magnetic domains within a material to the applied magnetic field, i.e., the alignment of the magnetic domains and the stregnth of the total induced magnetic field in the material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> "B")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> (remanence)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "remanence"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "remnant Induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "Remanence is the magnetic induction B that remains in the material when the magnetic field strength H is reduced to zero."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> "Br"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000050> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> (saturation induction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "saturation induction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "saturation magnetic flux density"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "Saturation induction is a magnetic property which is stimulated under an application of magnetic field. It characterizes the maximum induction B a material can achieve, i.e., the saturation induction is reached when it remains unchanged with increasing magnetic field strength H."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "Bmax")
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> "Bsat"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000049>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> (magnetic permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> "magnetic permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> "Magnetic permeability is a magnetic property that measures ability of a material to support the formation of a magnetic field within itself, and can be determined as the ratio between magnetic flux density / induction B and applied magnetic field strength H (μ=B/H)."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> (magnetic power loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> "magnetic power loss"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> "Magnetic power loss is a magnetic property of materials which describes dissipated energy due to application of an external magnetic field H."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> (anomalous loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "Anamalous loss is propotional to the frequency of the alternating magnetic field f^3/2."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "Anomalous loss can be reduced byy minimizing domain wall spacing to ensure more uniform magnetization. This can be achieved by controlling grain size and crystallographic texure."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "anomalous loss"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "Anomalous loss is a type of a magnetic power loss which is determined as a difference between total magnetic power loss P_tot and the sum of both hysteresis loss P_hys and eddy current loss  P_e. Anomalous loss is attributed to the localized, microscopic eddy currents generated by the motion of individual magnetic domain walls."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> "P_a")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000054> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(ObjectInverseOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055>) <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> (eddy current loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "Eddy current loss can be reduced by using thinner sheets and increasing Si content, which raises resistivity ρ."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "The value of eddy current loss is proportional to the alternating frequency of an applied magnetic field f, sheet thickness d, and the peak induction Bsat, and inversely proportinal to the electric resistivity ρ. 
Pe∝f2⋅d2⋅Bp2​/ρ"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "eddy current loss"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "Eddy current loss is a type of magnetic power loss which is attributed to the macroscopic circulating electrical currents which are induced  by the change of the magnetic flux dB/dt in the bulk of a material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> "P_e")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000055> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> (hysteresis loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> "Hysteresis loss can be reduced by controlling chemical composition, i.e., reducing nonmetallic impurities and increasing Si content, and by controlling microstructure, i.e., achieving large uniform grains with minimizing inclusions and precipitates."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> "hysteresis loss"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> "Hysteresis loss is a type of magnetic power lossses attributed dissipation of energy due to the irreversible motion of a magnetic domain wall. The value of hystereis loss is equivalent to the area of a static B-H curve."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> "Phys"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000056> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(ObjectInverseOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055>) <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000021>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> (total magnetic power loss)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> "Total magnetic power loss is magnetic property of a material which describes its performance in an external magnetic field. Total magnetic power loss is a sum of hysteresis P_hys, eddy current P_e, and anomalous losses P_a."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> "total magnetic power loss"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> "P_tot"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000057> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000053>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> (electrical resistivity)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> "electrical resistivity"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> "The electrical resistivity is an electrical property describing the ability of a material to oppose the flow of electric current. It is reciprocal to electric conductivity."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000058> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000621>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> (differential permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "Derivative dB/dH"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "differential permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "Differential permeability is the instantaneous slope of the magnetization curve or hysteresis loop at any given point"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> "µd"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000059> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> (incremental permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> "incremental permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(owl:deprecated <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> "")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000060> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> (initial permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "How easily the material magnetizes from rest"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "initial permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "Initial permeability characterizes the slope of the tangent to the magnetization curve at the origin, i.e., H=0 and B=0. It represents the permeability in the weakest magnetic fields"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> "µi"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000061> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> (maximum permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "The maximum value of the normal permeability (the steepest line from the origin to the magnetization curve)."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "maximum permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "Maximum permeability is the steepest part of the B-H curve, where the material most readily accepts field. it indicates the easiest magnetization point of the material,"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> "µmax"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000062> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> (normal permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "A line from the origin to the loop tip"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "normal permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "Normal permeabilty is the ratio of the peak magnetic induction B_max to the peak magnetic field strength H_max for a specific magnitization cycle."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> "μa"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000063> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> (reversible permeability)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> "reversible permeability"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(owl:deprecated <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000064> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000052>)

