# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000117> (rolling mill)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000117> "rolling mill"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000117> "Rolling mill is device which is a participant in a rolling process, has a function of reducing thickness of an object that is specified input to the rolling process, and this function is realized in the rolling process."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000117> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000117> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000118> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000118> (thickness reduction function)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000118> "thickness reduction function"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000118> "Thickness reduction function is a function to reduce thickness of a material."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000118> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000034>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000119> (number of rolling passes)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000119> "Number of rolling passes is a process attribute of a rolling process which specifies how many times a piece of material have been passed between rolling mills to achieve desired thickness."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000119> "number of rolling passes"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000119> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000119> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>) ObjectAllValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000023>)))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000123> (deviation angle)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000123> "TODO axiom")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000123> "deviation angle"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000123> "Deviation angle is a geometric relational quality relevant for the crystallographic texture analysis. Deviation angle  represents an angle between two crystallographic planes which are denoted by the same Miller indices, namely a crystallographic plane which is perfectly parallel to the rolling plane of a sheet material and a crystallographic plane in a crystal grain which is a part of the material."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000123> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025018>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000153> (diffraction process)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000153> "diffraction process"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000153> "Diffraction process is a structural property analyzing process which utilizes diffraction of either electron, x-ray, or neutron waves to determine material's crystal structure, crystallographic texture, (phase) composition, and presence of defects."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000153> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000957>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000154> (diffractometer)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000154> "diffractometer"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000154> "Diffractometer is a device which detects the intensity of a beam of either electrons, x-rays, or neutrons scattered from a material during a diffraction process."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000154> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000155> (EBSD system)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000155> "EBSD system"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000155> "Electron backscatter diffraction (EBSD) system is a diffractomter which detects diffracted electrons in the chamber of a scanning electron microscope."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000155> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000154>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156> (maximal magnetic field strength)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156> "maximal magnetic field strength"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156> "Maximal magnetic field is a maximal value of a magnetic field has has to be achieved during characterization of magnetic properties"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156> "Hmax"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000156> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000070>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000159> (electron microscope accelerating voltage)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000159> "electron microscope accelerating voltage"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000159> "Electron microscope accelerating voltage is a process attribute of an electron microscopy assay which describes the value of a voltage applied to the electron source to extract electrons from the source and accelerate them in the direction of a sample"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000159> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000159> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000625>))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> (angle to rolling direction)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> "TODO refine the axiom: 
1. Add reference frames for sample and material?
2. longitudinal direction as sublcass of fiat line?")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> "angle to rolling direction"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> "Angle to rolling direction is a relational quality which characterizes the orientation of a sample cut from a rolled material in respect to the rolling direction (RD) of this material."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> "Sample cut at 30° to rolling direction of a annealed nonoriented electrical steel."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025018>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000160> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000031> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000074> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030>))) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025999> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000033> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000074> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>)))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> (α*-fibre grain orientation)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> "The axiom is not expressible in OWL. 
TODO: write a SWIRL rule"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> "α*-fibre grain orientation"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> "{h11}<1/h12>")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> "α*-fibre grain orientation is a type of grain orientation which is quality of polycrystal, i.e., several grains, oriented in the following way: {11h} family of crystallographic planes are oriented parallel to the rolling plane of a sheet material and <1/h12> family of crystallographic directions are oriented parallel to the rolling direction (RD) of a sheet material."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000161> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000853>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000163> (magnetic properties measuring device)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000163> "magnetic properties measuring device"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000163> "Magnetic properties measuring device is a device that measures a hysteresis curve, i,e., its corresponding characteristic points, hysteresis loss, and total magnetic loss, of soft magnetic materials by applying alternating (AC) or quasi-static (DC) electric current on copper coils to produde external magnetic field."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000163> "Single sheet tester (SST), Epstein frame, Ring core tester"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000163> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000165> (fillet radius)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000165> "fillet radius"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000165> "Fillet radus is a charactereristic paramater of a geometry of a tensile test specimen which characterizes the radius of the curved sections (fillets) connecting the gripping ends to the reduced gauge length in a standard \"dog-bone\" specimen is specifically dimensioned to prevent stress concentrations from causing premature failure outside the gauge length."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000165> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0040001>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000166> (average grain size)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000166> "average grain size"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000166> "Average grain size is an intensive quality of a material which describes the average diameter of grains in the material's microstructure."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000166> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177> (grain population)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177> "Grain population is a disconnected material aggregate which has crystallites ias parts.  Grain population represents grains which not necesserly spatially connected (unlike polycrystal) but share some collective quality, such as preffered crystallographic orientation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177> "grain population"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000177> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> (magnetic polarization)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> "TODO add axioms
1. When the magnetic qualities are realized
2. Especially for peak values that would be interesting"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> "magnetic polarization"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> "Magnetic polarization is a magnetic property which is a measure of intrinsic magnetization of a material (alignment of magnetic dipoles) as a response to the externaly applied magnetic field H. It is determined as a difference between magnetic induction B and the external field µ0*H."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/symbol> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> "J")
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000178> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000825>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> (electrical steel)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> "Electrical steel is a steel material which has only ferritic metallic grain structure and uses silicon as the main alloying element. It manufactured in a form of a sheet and designed to exibit superior magenetic properties either in all directions (non-orieneted) or in a sinlge direction (oriented)."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> "electrical steel"@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020096>)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020050>))
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000857> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025003> ObjectHasValue(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020100>))))))

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> (non-oriented electrical steel)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> "non-oriented electrical steel"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> "NOES")
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> "Non-oriented electrical steel is an electrical steel material which exhibits isotropic magnetic properties in all direction in the sheet plane."@en)
SubClassOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000179>)

# Class: <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000181> (NO27-14)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000181> "TODO: 
1. Import W/kg units
2. Add units to the equivalent class
3. Think of adding nomical thickness class
4. Check the some in the decimal"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000181> "NO27-14"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000181> "NO27-14 is a non-oriented electrical steel which has characteristic total magnetic losses P1.0/400 of max 14 W/kg and a quality thickness of 0.27 mm."@en)
EquivalentClasses(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000181> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000180> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/noes/NOES_0000069> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> DataSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001937> DatatypeRestriction(xsd:decimal xsd:maxInclusive "14.0"^^xsd:decimal)))))) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ObjectIntersectionOf(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050153> ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077> ObjectIntersectionOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001931> DataSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001937> DatatypeRestriction(xsd:decimal xsd:minInclusive "0.27"^^xsd:decimal))))))))
